SIMPLE: sticker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sticker
<hw>Stick"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, sticks; <as>as, a bill <ex>sticker</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which causes one to stick; that which puzzles
or poses.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Tackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>In the organ, a small wooden rod
which connects (in part) a key and a pallet, so as to communicate motion
by pushing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Same as <er>Paster</er>, 2.</def> <mark>[Political
Cant, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stickful</ent>⟦br⟧
